*flightgear-0.9.6 (21 Oct 2004)

  21 Oct 2004; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  -flightgear-0.9.3.ebuild, flightgear-0.9.4.ebuild,
  +flightgear-0.9.5.ebuild, +flightgear-0.9.6.ebuild:
  removed 0.9.3, and moved 0.9.4 to stable x86. Now, 0.9.5 came from Alonso
  Schaich <AlonsoSchaich@gmx.de> in bug #59001 and compiles cleanly with
  gcc-3.4. Version 0.9.6 came from Adam Babcock <ababcock@sympatico.ca> in bug
  #67809. I personally had problems with 0.9.6 and found 0.9.5 to be much
  better, but your mileage may vary. For this reason, I have added both, and I
  expect to hear from the gamers which version is the superior. So bug report
  me please

  11 Jun 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  flightgear-0.9.4.ebuild:
  ~amd64 for bug #52454

  12 May 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  flightgear-0.9.4.ebuild:
  broken makefiles - -j1 for bug #50671

  06 May 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  flightgear-0.9.3.ebuild, flightgear-0.9.4.ebuild:
  IUSE; use emake or fail

  14 Apr 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org>
  flightgear-0.9.4.ebuild:
  this version's configure looks for plib >= 1.7.0; fix deps (bug #47855)

  12 Apr 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> flightgear-0.9.4.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword.

